Ugandan inflation accelerated to
14.1 percent in April as food costs surged, the Uganda Bureau of
Statistics said.  Food prices rose 30.8 percent from a year earlier, the
Kampala-based agency said in a statement handed to reporters
today. Inflation rose 3 percent in the month, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
